            }
        }
        cout << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This program will display an ASCII representation of the normal distribution of the `arr` array using asterisks for points on the curve and blank spaces for points below the curve. The mean and variance of the array are calculated, and the normal distribution function is used to determine the height of the curve at each point. The x and y increments are determined by the width and height of the display.
